In contrast to Janice, Frank is a prime example of a person who dies by suicide in the United States, wherein men—particularly white males—dominate suicide deaths. Frank’s history of depression, alcohol abuse, isolation, and job troubles are all worrisome. Immediately concerning is his purchase of a handgun (the number one method for suicide in the United States); his preparatory behavior of writing suicide notes is also troubling. However, Frank’s lack of any previous suicide attempts is encouraging and the relative “newness” of his suicidal thinking make him an especially good candidate for CAMS which can be safely rendered on an outpatient basis (Jobes,
               2023
            ).
